# Line-ending policy.
#
# Windows-only scripts MUST have CRLF. cmd.exe and PowerShell are strict —
# LF-only line endings produce silent or fragmented errors. See the launcher
# breakage on 2026-05-18 where every .bat / .ps1 in startup/ committed with
# LF caused "_detect-python.bat not recognized" and word-fragment errors
# (e / op / can / d) because cmd's parser was glueing tokens across LF
# boundaries.

# Windows shell scripts → always CRLF, even on Linux check-outs.
*.bat       text eol=crlf
*.cmd       text eol=crlf
*.ps1       text eol=crlf

# Default text: let git normalise (auto-detect on checkin, native on checkout).
*           text=auto

# Binaries: never touch line endings.
*.parquet   binary
*.gz        binary
*.zip       binary
*.png       binary
*.ico       binary
*.svg       binary
